       Phrases like &quot;my bad&quot; and words like Dude are not what I would call part of the English/American language.  They are just words used by young adults, teenagers to differentiate themselves form the adults, to be &quot;cool&quot;(another word whose meaning has been changed and has become international)<br>
   Certain things though do not stay around, they're used for a while but then you don't hear them anymore and new phrases and words are invented. <br>
    For example, groovy was popular in the 60's, then cool came along to replace it, then cool got lost for a while and then came back.  What next?  who knows!<br>
